> Great for grilling! We've put together all the fixins for a full-on barbecue feast:
> sticky baby back ribs and saucy BBQ pulled chicken sandwiches. Grill up the ribs
> and chicken in foil packets, or use your oven and stovetop—either way, you'll
> have your BBQ fix in no time!

== Ribs ==

Remove @BBQ Baby Back Ribs{24%ounce} from package, reserving any extra sauce.
Place on a lightly oiled piece of #foil{} large enough to wrap around ribs.
Brush tops of ribs with remaining sauce. Tightly crimp foil to form a packet.

GRILL: Place foil packet on #grill{} grates over medium heat; close grill. Cook
until ribs are warmed through, ~{20-25%minutes}. Remove ribs from packet. Cut
between bones into desired number of portions and drizzle with any remaining
sauce from packet.

OVEN: Place foil packet on a #baking sheet{}. Bake at 400° until ribs are warmed
through and edges are lightly caramelized, ~{22-25%minutes}. Remove ribs from
packet. Cut between bones into desired number of portions and drizzle with any
remaining sauce from packet.

== BBQ Pulled Chicken ==

Remove @Pulled Chicken in BBQ Sauce{20%ounce} from package, reserving any extra
sauce. Place on a lightly-oiled piece of foil large enough to wrap around
chicken. Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Tightly crimp foil to form a packet.
Halve @Brioche Buns{4}.

GRILL: Place foil packet on grill grates over medium heat; close grill. Cook
until chicken is warmed through, ~{6-8%minutes}. In the last ~{2-3%minutes} of
cooking, grill buns. Assemble into sandwiches.

STOVETOP: Heat a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Cook until chicken is warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Toast
buns. Assemble into sandwiches.